node.title: Miami Resident Latest Suspect Detained in Connection to Haitian President Moïse's Assassination
node.alt: Another suspect was arrested in connection to the killing of Haitian President Jovenel Moise. Here, Moise speaks onstage at the Grand Hyatt New York on September 25, 2018 in New York City.
node.description: So far, more than 40 suspects have been detained in connection to Moïse's death, but police have not yet determined a motive.
node.content:
["Another suspect connected with the July assassination of Haitian President Jovenel Mo\u00efse was arrested this week in Turkey, according to Haiti's foreign affairs minister.", "Samir Handal was arrested at the Istanbul airport on Sunday night after arriving on a Turkish Airlines flight. Handal, a businessman and builder from Haiti, had been living in Miami after the July 7 killing of Mo\u00efse.", "Handal has allegedly been connected to Christian Emmanuel Sanon, a 62-year-old Haitian doctor and South Florida resident who is also accused of being involved in the assassination, the Miami Herald reported. On Monday, Haitian Foreign Affairs Minister Claude Joseph tweeted his thanks to Turkish officials for conducting the latest arrest.", "\"I just had a phone conversation with the Turkish Chancellor, my friend @MevlutCavusoglu, to thank Turkey for the arrest of Samir Handal, one of the people of great interest in the investigation into the assassination of the president @moisejovenel,\" Joseph said.", "Mo\u00efse was killed in July by several gunmen who stormed his residence in the Haitian capital, Port-au-Prince. His wife, Martine Mo\u00efse, was also injured during the attack but survived.", "So far, more than 40 suspects have been detained in connection to Mo\u00efse's death, but police have not yet determined a motive.", "This is a breaking news story and will be updated as more information becomes available.
